ing clear to the cadet that she or he has the primary responsibility for managing his or her education        In order to mentor  support and challenge advisees  the advisor will  Monitor cadet academic progress via face to face and electronic interaction  Mentor cadet by providing accurate and timely information in a professional and friendly manner  Review the Program Evaluation  periodically and in response to cadet inquiry   Refer cadets to VMI support services  as needed  Maintain regular office hours   Attend relevant advisor development opportunities  Remain current on standards and regulations which impact cadet   Encourage cadets to take responsibility for accomplishing all goals by requiring increasing levels of pre advising cadet preparation and self monitoring over the course of the cadetship   Make a reasonable attempt to follow up with absentee cadets  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 